description: Check the electrical continuity and reliability of the cables and fast-connection terminals connecting the control module to the load module. Wiggle or move the connections while monitoring the lamp operation for any change in the flickering/off behavior., outcome='All continuity measurements show nominal resistance values (0.1 Ω) for both the control and load cables, indicating proper electrical continuity. No wiring faults or disruptions were detected during testing. No polarity inversion has been reported in these steps.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Ambient light sensor and sensitivity potentiometer in Control Module,
description: Test the output of the ambient light sensor and adjust the sensitivity potentiometer. Monitor whether the relay status changes and if the lamp responds (turns off/on) accordingly. Check if the sensor or potentiometer is causing intermittent relay behavior., outcome='The ambient light sensor is providing a low voltage output (0.119 V at positive terminal, 0.0003 V at negative terminal) when measured. The relay is observed to be closed, but the main lamp is not lit. Both the ambient light sensor and the sensitivity potentiometer have been marked for further hypothesis verification as possible sources of intermittent relay behavior.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=340.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('verify_repair', 120.0), ('verify_repair', 120.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Lamp indicator and main lamp in Load Module,
description: Directly measure the voltage across both the main lamp and the lamp indicator in the load module while the system is operating, particularly during the off period. This will help determine if the issue is with voltage delivery to the bulbs, a possible diode issue, or a lamp fault., outcome='Both the main lamp and the internal indicator lamp show almost zero voltage at both the positive and negative terminals during the off period. This suggests that neither bulb is receiving significant voltage while the system is off. No polarity inversion is detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply to Control Module input terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the power supply output and at the Control Module input during the lamp's off period and when it turns on. This will help determine if the supply voltage is stable and being reliably delivered to the Control Module, or if there is a supply dropout or intermittent connection upstream of the relay., outcome='The voltage at the PSU Output Cable (+) and Control Input Cable (+) is approximately 11.99 V, while the voltage at the (-) cables is approximately 0 V. There are no polarity inversions detected between the PSU output and the Control Module input cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module output terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the output terminals of the Control Module (the switched side, before entering the Load Module) during both the 'on' and 'off' periods of the lamp cycle. This will help determine if the voltage is being interrupted at the control module output side, which could point to relay control circuit or internal faults., outcome="Voltage at 'Control Output Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V, and at 'Control Output Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V. The measured voltages are very low at both terminals relative to ground. No polarity inversion detected based on current cable labeling.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched Cables Indicator Circuit in Control Module,
description: Test the voltage across the switched cables indicator LED and its associated resistor in the control module, both during the lamp's 'on' and 'off' periods. This will help determine if the circuit is correctly indicating power delivery and whether there is a hidden issue with switching or with the indicator circuit itself., outcome='The PSU Status LED (green) has an anode voltage of 1.2916 V and a cathode voltage of 0.0 V, indicating typical LED operation. The PSU Green LED Resistor shows a voltage drop from 11.9876 V to 1.2916 V, confirming current flow across the resistor and LED. No polarity inversion was detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=50.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched Cables Indicator LED and Output Path (Control Module),
description: Directly measure voltage at the anode and cathode of the switched cables indicator LED and along the relay output path (between relay output and the output terminals) during both the lamp's 'on' and 'off' periods. This will help determine if there is a failure in the indicator circuit or a break/open circuit immediately downstream of the relay., outcome='The PSU Status LED (green) anode reads 1.2916 V and cathode 0.0 V, indicating typical LED forward bias. The Control Relay has 11.9873 V at its positive terminal and 0.3592 V at negative, while the Control Output Cable (+) shows only 0.3592 V and the Control Output Cable (−) shows 0.0003 V at both terminals. No polarity inversion is detected between the control cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=85.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module internal PCB traces and solder joints (Relay output to output terminals),
description: Inspect and test the continuity between the relay's switched (output) contact and the control module output terminals. Use a multimeter to check for high resistance or open circuits on the internal PCB traces or solder joints. Look for signs of broken tracks, cold joints, or disconnections between the relay output and the output connectors., outcome='All connections inspected between the relay and control output cables match expected polarity—no polarity inversion detected. Continuity tests show a short (0.01 Ω) on the positive path and a resistive (1.40 Ω) connection on the negative path. No visual internal faults were found on the relay or output cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Relay output contact and switched circuit path (internal to Control Module),
description: Test for any voltage drop or abnormal resistance between the relay's switched output contact and the internal PCB trace leading to the control module's output connector. Check if there is a hidden issue such as a partially conductive or corroded junction that could explain the persistent low voltage despite visual inspection and continuity tests., outcome='The voltage at the Control Relay is 11.9873 V (positive terminal) and 0.3592 V (negative terminal), but the Control Output Cable (+) shows both terminals at 0.3592 V. Point-to-point continuity between the Control Relay and the Control Output Cable (+) is confirmed as a short (R=0.01 Ω). The data indicates a significant voltage drop between the relay output and the cable, with no abnormal resistance detected along the path.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=75.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Relay switched contact (output path, Control Module) and external fast connection terminal,
description: Directly measure voltage between the relay's output contact (after switch) and the immediate external terminal for Control Output Cable (+), while ensuring the system is operating. This isolates whether the voltage drop occurs at the PCB-to-connector junction, the PCB trace, or the terminal/connector itself., outcome='The voltage at the relay output contact is 11.9873\u202fV (positive), but at the Control Output Cable (+) terminal, the voltage drops to 0.3592\u202fV. This shows a significant voltage drop between the relay output and the cable terminal.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Mechanical interface between relay output pin and PCB socket/through-hole,
description: Visually and physically inspect the mechanical interface where the relay output pin is inserted into and soldered/connected to the PCB trace, looking for hairline cracks, partial insertions, corrosion, intermittent contact, or physical stress that may not be electrically obvious during static tests., outcome="Inspection of the mechanical interface at the relay output pin did not reveal any observable internal faults or issues with the physical connections. Both port 'p' and port 'n' on the Control Relay are connected to cables labeled with (+), and no polarity inversion is present.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Relay output contact (Control Module) and PCB copper at various distances from the contact,
description: With the system powered and relay closed, measure the voltage at the relay output pin itself and then at consecutive points along the PCB trace from the pin towards the output terminal, looking for where the voltage drop occurs. This can reveal if there is an internal PCB layer or via failure, or a hidden break in a multi-layer or hidden section of trace., outcome='There is a significant voltage drop between the relay output pin (11.99 V) and the Control Output Cable (+) (0.36 V). This suggests there may be a break or failure in the PCB trace or an internal connection between these two points.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> PCB vias and multi-layer connections (between relay output and output terminal, Control Module),
description: Systematically probe the voltage at both sides of any vias, jumper wires, or board-to-board connectors (if any) along the positive trace between the relay output and the Control Output Cable terminal. Look for a specific via or connector where the high-side voltage abruptly drops, indicating an internal or hidden open circuit not obvious from surface inspection., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> PCB trace and via continuity (between relay output and output terminal, Control Module),
description: Use a continuity test mode to probe the entire trace length from the relay output pin to the output terminal, including across any visible or suspect vias. This targets confirming a hidden open or high-resistance segment in a multilayer trace or via that may intermittently bridge under some circumstances., outcome='Continuity test between the Control Relay and Control Output Cable (+) shows a short path with very low resistance (0.01 Ω). This indicates continuous, low-resistance connectivity across the measured trace segment. No polarity inversion detected in this connection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Battery negative (Power Supply) to control output negative (Control Module) path,
description: Test the voltage and continuity from battery negative terminal through the negative (ground) side of the circuit to the output negative terminal of the Control Module. This checks whether there is an open/high resistance in the negative supply return path, which could cause abnormal voltage readings on positive paths and low voltage at the output., outcome='The negative (ground) return path from the battery through the PSU Output Cable (−), Control Input Cable (−), and Control Output Cable (−) shows very low resistance and no open circuits, confirming continuity throughout. No polarity inversion is detected among the cables in this negative supply path. Voltage readings on all negative terminals are consistent and close to ground.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=180.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module (internal, between relay output and Switched Cables Indicator LED / Output Path),
description: Systematically check for unexpected parallel loads or hidden elements (e.g., unintended short, damaged component, or solder bridge) between the relay switched output and the output terminal/indicator circuit, by measuring resistance with the system powered off. This may reveal a shunt path that could explain the voltage drop from relay output (high) to output terminal (low) in spite of confirmed continuity when unpowered., outcome='All continuity measurements indicate expected results: Control Relay to Control Output Cable (+) and Load Input Cable (+) both show very low resistance (short), while connections to the Main Load lamp and Internal Indicator Lamp show appropriate resistive values (~98 Ω). The path from Control Relay to Load Protection Diode also reports a low resistance (0.21 Ω), consistent with a diode in parallel with the load. No evidence of unexpected parallel shunt paths or hidden shorts between relay output and output terminal/indicator circuits was found.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=170.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
